  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dd6\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0dd9\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0db6\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Division of Urea Fertilizer is over",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Agriculture says that the government has successfully completed the distribution of urea fertilizer brought to Sri Lanka under an Indian loan scheme for the 2022 yala season.",
        "Thus Uva province 2122 metric tons, Western province 1041 metric tons, Central province 2138 metric tons, North-western province 3767 metric tons, Sabaragamuwa province 1128 metric tons, Southern province 4728 metric tons, Northern province 877 metric tons, Eastern province 3934 metric tons. Also distributed.",
        "Accordingly, the Department of Agricultural Development emphasized that the total amount of urea fertilizer distributed to 490,515 farmers who cultivated 304,734 hectares is 29,740.73 metric tons."
      ],
